value.value: Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the elongated, curved bones forming the bony wall of the chest.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the process by which the right and left sides of the heart become separated.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the rib structures near the spine; ribs do not contact vertebrae.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the attachment of ribs to the vertebral column or to the sternum.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the long, flat bone of the chest.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the posterior/inferior tip of the sternum.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the nonvascular, resilient, flexible connective tissue found primarily in joints, walls of the thorax, and tubular structures, but which also comprises most of the skeleton in early fetal life; some species have skeletons that are completely composed of cartilage which is never ossified.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the morphology or physiology during formation and differentiation of the nonvascular, resilient, flexible connective tissue found primarily in joints, walls of the thorax, and tubular structures, but which also comprises most of the skeleton in early fetal life. Some aquatic vertebrates have skeletons comprised entirely of cartilage.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the layer of the epiphyseal plate where no cell division occurs and chondrocytes begin to terminally differentiate.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of non-dividing cartilage cells.
The proportion or number of non-dividing cartilage cells.
Any measurable characteristic related to the function of or processes in the tubular channels through which the blood circulates.

Any measurable functional characteristic related to the function of or processes in the fluid that circulates through the heart, arteries, veins, and capillaries, carrying oxygen and nutritive materials and removing waste products and carbon dioxide.
The proportion or number of cells that make up the core cavities of bones.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the function of or processes in the lymph vessels.

Any measurable functional characteristic related to the function of or processes in the fluid which is collected from the tissues throughout the body, flows in the lymphatic vessels, and is eventually added to the venous blood circulation.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the circulation of blood throughout the body, including both the movement and the forces created by the movement.

The proportion, quantity, or volume in whole blood, serum, or plasma of the most abundant steroid in animal tissues, and precursor to steroid hormones and bile salts; also component of plasma membranes.

The proportion, quantity, or volume in whole blood, serum, or plasma of the lipoprotein: cholesterol complex that transports cholesterol out of the arteries and around the body, for use by various tissues in normal bodily functions.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the movement of blood within a vessel or tissue.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the hydrostatic force exerted by the blood perpendicular to the blood-tissue surface.

The proportion, quantity, or volume in whole blood, serum, or plasma of the small lipoprotein:cholesterol complex that transports cholesterol out of the arteries and to the liver for reprocessing or excretion.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the mechanical force exerted by the blood parallel to the blood-tissue surface.

The proportion, quantity, or volume in a body tissue or fluid of this molecule, glycerol esterified at each of its three hydroxyl groups by a fatty acid; triglyceride is an important molecule for storage of fatty acids in adipose tissue.

The proportion, quantity, or volume in whole blood, serum, or plasma of the monosaccharide that is the end product of carbohydrate digestion; D-glucose serves as a primary energy source for living organisms.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the ability of the blood vessels (tubular channels through which the blood circulates) to stretch.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the ability of gases, liquids, or solutes to pass through the blood vessel wall.
The proportion, quantity, or volume in a body tissue or fluid of any inorganic element or compound that has importance in body functions.
Any measurable characteristic related to the ability of a blood vessel to change diameter in response to a chemical or mechanical signal.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the ability of a blood vessel to increase its diameter in response to a chemical or mechanical signal.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the ability of a blood vessel to reduce its diameter in response to a chemical or mechanical signal.

The proportion, quantity, or volume in whole blood, serum, or plasma of the major blood protein that is important in maintenance of the colloidal osmotic pressure, fatty acid transport, and transport of large organic molecules.
The proportion, quantity, or volume in whole blood, serum, or plasma of this enzyme, which hydrolyzes orthophosphoric monoesters.

The proportion, quantity, or volume in whole blood, serum, or plasma of this enzyme, which catalyzes the reversible transfer of an amine group from l-glutamic acid to oxaloacetic acid, forming alpha-ketoglutaric acid and l-aspartic acid; aids in diagnosis of viral hepatitis and myocardial infarction.
The proportion or number of nucleated cells of the myeloid or lymphoid lineages, found in blood or other tissue.
The proportion or number of the granular leukocytes that have a three- to five-lobed nucleus and a cytoplasm containing inconspicuous granules.
The proportion or number of large, phagocytic mononuclear leukocytes produced in the vertebrate bone marrow and released into the blood.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to development of the non-nucleated cells of the blood (platelets, thrombocytes) involved in blood coagulation.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the morphology or physiology during formation and differentiation of these very large bone marrow cells which release mature platelets.
Any measurable characteristic related to the function of or processes involved in generation and conduction of electrical impulses in the heart.
The proportion or numbers of the various types of blood cells.
The proportion or number of the hematopoietic stem cells that are capable of forming any of the myeloid lineage cells.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the physical site where formation and development of blood cells occurs.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the generation of action potentials in cardiac muscle.
Any measurable characteristic related to the function of or processes in the formation of red blood cells.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the physical magnitude of the cells in the blood that carry oxygen, red blood cells

The proportion, quantity, or volume of the serum-like fluid that circulates through the ventricles of the brain, the cavity of the spinal cord, and the subarachnoid space, functioning in shock absorption.
Any measurable functional characteristic related to blood flow in a specific region of the body, tissue, or organ.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the ability of gases, liquids, or solutes to pass through the capillary wall.
Any measurable functional characteristic related to the process of prevention of blood loss.
